Fire has razed a residential storey-building of three flats in Ilorin, Kwara State/ The fire disaster occurred at Igbala close, Stadium Road area, in Ilorin metropolis. According to a statement by the spokesman of the State Fire Service, Hassan Hakeem Adekunle, the incident occurred as a result of a power surge. He revealed that firefighters also found a pressing iron plugged in a socket during the rescue operation. He said, “The lead officer of the firemen, who led the rescue operation, revealed that although the fire was caused by a power surge, a pressing iron was also plugged in,” the spokesman said. Hakeem said while the conflagration was huge, firefighters were, however, able to extinguish the fire in no time. Out of the three flats in the building, only one flat was consumed by the inferno and the two remaining ones were rescued by the firemen.